<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="17" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1436,1727,1962]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[208,336,1769,1795]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Body vermiform; opisthosoma with setae 
<emphasis box="[845,872,1769,1794]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">c1</emphasis>
; prodorsal shield with 2 anterior setae (
<emphasis box="[1349,1375,1769,1794]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">ve</emphasis>
) and glands, scapular setae (
<emphasis box="[428,452,1811,1836]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">sc</emphasis>
) and tubercles on rear prodorsal shield margin, minute; coxae I and coxae II each with 3 setae; legs with usual segmentation and setae.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="17" type="discussion">
